## Example entries (✅ good — keep this style)

### INFRA-001 — Primary application database
- **Type:** database
- **Provider + region:** AWS RDS PostgreSQL, us-east-1
- **Version / SKU:** PostgreSQL 16.2, db.m5.large, gp3 200GB
- **Used by:** all backend services (`finance.*`, `orders.*`, `customers.*` schemas); read-only consumers via dedicated replica
- **Operational facts designers need:**
  - `max_connections: 200`; reserve 20 for migrations and dba — apps share 180 via PgBouncer (`statement` mode).
  - All financial tables (schema `finance.*`) are append-only — UPDATE/DELETE revoked at DB level (see BR-001).
  - Backup window: 03:00-04:00 UTC daily; PITR retention: 7 days; cross-region snapshot weekly to us-west-2.
  - Replicas: 1 read-replica in same AZ; designs for read-heavy workloads should target the replica explicitly via separate connection string.
- **HA / failover:** Multi-AZ enabled; automatic failover ~60-90s; client app retries handled at HikariCP layer.
- **Connection point (sanitized):** `<env>-db.<region>.rds.amazonaws.com:5432`; resolved via `DB_HOST` env var (see `application-{profile}.properties`).
- **Owner (internal):** alice (DBA-equivalent); on-call for paging events.
- **Cost dependency:** [[cost-constraints]] CC-003 (RDS storage scaling).
- **Related:** [[vendor-relationships]] VR-001 (AWS as cloud provider), ADR-006 (single primary DB vs distributed), BR-001 (append-only events), [[incident-log]] INC-002 (2024 failover incident that established the 60-90s expectation).
- **Captured:** 2025-10-15 by alice

### INFRA-005 — S3 uploads bucket
- **Type:** storage
- **Provider + region:** AWS S3, us-east-1 (primary)
- **Version / SKU:** S3 Standard for first 90 days, Standard-IA after 90, Glacier after 365
- **Used by:** UploadService for customer-uploaded documents (KYC IDs, invoice attachments); read by AdminPortal for audit
- **Operational facts designers need:**
  - Lifecycle: 90d Standard → IA → 365d Glacier; **never** delete (LGPD audit requirement; see BR-019).
  - Object-key convention: `<tenant_id>/<yyyy>/<mm>/<uuid>-<sanitized-filename>`; never expose raw key in URLs (signed URLs only, 15-min TTL).
  - Cross-region replication to us-west-2 enabled for KYC subfolder only (regulatory).
  - Bucket policy: deny `s3:DeleteObject` for all principals except `dba-break-glass` role.
- **HA / failover:** S3 native; no client failover logic needed.
- **Connection point (sanitized):** `s3://<env>-<app>-uploads/`; resolved via `S3_UPLOADS_BUCKET` env var.
- **Owner (internal):** alice; renewal N/A (per-request pricing).
- **Cost dependency:** [[cost-constraints]] CC-004 (S3 lifecycle cost; cross-region replication cost watch).
- **Related:** [[vendor-relationships]] VR-001 (AWS), BR-019 (LGPD upload retention), ADR-011 (signed URL pattern for uploads).
- **Captured:** 2025-10-15 by alice

